<h2>Step 2: Verify Face Against Document</h2>

<p>Compare the user's selfie against the photo extracted from the document:</p>

<pre><code>const result = await ob.documents.verify(selfieImage, documentImage);

if (result.is_match) {'{'}
  console.log(`Match: ${'{'}(result.similarity * 100).toFixed(1){'}'}%`);
{'}'} else {'{'}
  // Reject: face doesn't match document
{'}'}
</code></pre>

<p>The API uses ArcFace embeddings (99.86% accuracy on LFW) to compare faces. A similarity threshold of 0.4 corresponds to roughly 1-in-a-million false match rate.</p>

<h2>Step 3: Liveness Detection</h2>

<p>The final step prevents spoofing — someone holding up a printed photo or showing a screen.</p>

<p><strong>Passive liveness</strong> (included in every detect call) catches basic attacks. For high-security KYC, use <strong>active liveness</strong> with challenge-response:</p>

<pre><code>// Create a liveness session
const session = await ob.liveness.createSession({'{'}
  challenges: ['blink', 'turn_left'],
  ttl_seconds: 120,
{'}'});

// Submit video frames as user completes challenges
const result = await ob.liveness.submitFrame(session.session_id, frame);

if (result.session_complete && result.is_live) {'{'}
  // User is verified as a real person
{'}'}
</code></pre>

<h2>Complete KYC Flow in 30 Lines</h2>

<pre><code>import OpenBiometrics from 'openbiometrics';

const ob = new OpenBiometrics({'{'} apiKey: process.env.OB_API_KEY {'}'});

async function verifyIdentity(documentImage, selfieImage, livenessFrames) {'{'}
  // 1. Scan document
  const doc = await ob.documents.scan(documentImage);
  if (!doc.mrz?.valid) throw new Error('Invalid document');

  // 2. Match face
  const match = await ob.documents.verify(selfieImage, documentImage);
  if (!match.is_match) throw new Error('Face mismatch');

  // 3. Liveness check
  const session = await ob.liveness.createSession({'{'}
    challenges: ['blink', 'smile'],
  {'}'});

  for (const frame of livenessFrames) {'{'}
    const result = await ob.liveness.submitFrame(session.session_id, frame);
    if (result.session_complete) {'{'}
      if (!result.is_live) throw new Error('Liveness failed');
      break;
    {'}'}
  {'}'}

  return {'{'}
    verified: true,
    name: `${'{'} doc.mrz.parsed.given_names {'}'} ${'{'} doc.mrz.parsed.surname {'}'}`,
    documentNumber: doc.mrz.parsed.document_number,
    similarity: match.similarity,
  {'}'};
{'}'}
</code></pre>

